parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag recall repair can lead to the airbag deploying improperly, causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag deploys without warning or impact
the airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag sensor remains illuminated
the airbag system fails to diagnose properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver, which can be dangerous and potentially fatal.
symptoms: The transmission makes a grinding or whining noise
the vehicle suddenly loses power
the transmission slips out of gear
the vehicle stalls
or the transmission seizes
causing the vehicle to come to a dead stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or strand the driver, which can be dangerous and potentially fatal.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.
